# Monolyth repo rules
- Do not create duplicate routes.
- API routes live under app/api/**.
- Public viewer is app/share/[id] (singular).
- Shares API is app/api/shares/* (plural).
- Events API is app/api/events/* (singular).
- DB columns: versions.doc_id; events.event_type (NOT NULL).
- Next.js 16: await params (params is a Promise).
- Prefer full-file replacements; keep styling minimal and consistent.

# If the misplaced file exists, move it to root:
if (Test-Path .husky\.cursorrules) { git mv .husky\.cursorrules .cursorrules }

# If it doesn’t exist there (or git mv fails), recreate it at root:
if (!(Test-Path .cursorrules)) {
@'
- API routes under app/api/**
- Public viewer: app/share/[id] (singular)
- Shares API: app/api/shares/* (plural)
- Events API: app/api/events/*
- DB columns: versions.doc_id; events.event_type (NOT NULL)
- Next.js 16: params is a Promise → await in dynamic routes
- Prefer full-file replacements
'@ | Out-File -Encoding utf8 .cursorrules
git add .cursorrules
}
